Professor Rotenberg is one of the best professors I've had. She is very clear at explaining concepts and is easy to understand. She cares about her students and makes sure no one falls behind. She marks fairly (B average). I would definitely recommend this course.

Lectures tended to be dry as she reads verbatim from lecture notes.   Doesn't seem to care about students as she never shows up while we write the exam (she said we can call her via cell phone in her office for questions).   Of concern is the competency  of MMPA director, Len Brooks and his hiring decisions.

Her grading is odd - if you make a calculation error in the beginning of the calculation, you will lose all marks assigned for further work on the question (rather than losing 1 point for a calculation error and getting points further downstream for work while propagating the error).  She insists on doing her own marking rather than hiring a TA
